Remember:
- In OS_Regex, \. matches ANY character; . matches a literal dot.
- NEVER use .* or .+ in OS_Regex. Use \.+ instead.
- Capture groups count MUST exactly match <order> field count.
- Always emit parent decoder BEFORE its child decoders.
- IP ADDRESS CRITICAL: ALWAYS use \d+.\d+.\d+.\d+ (plain dots).
  NEVER use \d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+ — that \. means ANY char, not a literal dot.
